<p>GHK-Cu is a copper-binding tripeptide with a molecular weight of just 403.9 g/mol. That small size is exactly why it penetrates the skin barrier so effectively. Studies confirm it reaches the dermis where it activates renewal pathways that thicker molecules simply cannot access.</p>

<p>Research published in the <em>Journal of Biomedicine and Biotechnology</em> shows GHK-Cu increases collagen production by up to 70%. A 2020 clinical trial found it significantly improved skin elasticity after 12 weeks, with participants reporting reduced wrinkles and better hydration.</p>

